               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-234-person2028">
                  HENRY 
                  BAKER
               <interp inst="t18321129-234-person2028" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-234-person2028" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-234-person2028" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. About eight o'clock in the evening of the 12th of November, I saw the prisoner and another loitering about the shop in Oxford-street - the other went in, and came out again; the prisoner then took the blind, and came out.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw a person come out of the shop with this blind - he ran, and placed it six doors off against a door-post; a woman said, "I think that man has been stealing something;" I went upto him - the Policeman came, and took me; I never touched the blind, and was not near it - I said, "You are mistaken;" he said," It does not matter, you will do quite as well," and then the woman who saw it followed us, making a noise, and kept saying, "That is not the man;" the officer threatened that if she followed him he would take her, or I should have had a witness here.</p>
